public class RemoteProtocolSessionImplementation
extends java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject
implements RemoteProtocolSessionInterface, java.rmi.server.Unreferenced

This class works as a remote wrapper to the local protocolSession It is sent as a callback interface to the yancees clients

unreferenced

public void unreferenced()
Implements the Unreferenced interface. This class is invoked by the Distributed Garbage Collector when the RMI reference counter for this object becomes 0 or when there is no communication for more than the lease period, which default timeout is 10 minutes. This method is used to release any resource allocated to this record which, in this case, is the protocol plug-in.

Specified by:
unreferenced in interface java.rmi.server.Unreferenced
